Police Minister Fikile Mbalula will on Tuesday visit tourists who were victims of robbery when they were travelling from OR Tambo International Airport to Fourways on a Megabus. It is alleged that 36 tourists who were travelling on a Megabus were stopped by a SAPS marked vehicle with one man dressed in SAPS uniform and five other civilians clothing. The men allegedly demanded their possessions and one of the tourists was injured and taken to the hospital. The men allegedly demanded their possessions and one of the tourists was injured and taken to the hospital. Mbalula has condemned the robbery on foreign tourists and views it as an attack on the tourism industry and the economy. “The OR Tambo International Airport is our national key point. We have done a lot of work to improve its safety and capacitate it to respond fast and effectively to safety concerns. More has been done since in preventing and combating criminal activities at the airport. The robbery in and around the OR Tambo International Airport is being investigated,” said Mbalula. “More has been done since in preventing and combating criminal activities at the airport. The robbery in and around the OR Tambo International Airport is being investigated,” said Mbalula. “Tourism is part of our economic drivers and provider of jobs for the youth, we must work hard in protecting this industry. Part of this is ensuring that our tourist not only feel safe but are safe in our country. I condemn this robbery in the strongest terms and call for harsh punishment on those responsible,” he added. Mbalula has instructed SAPS to investigate the matter and he has assured that detectives are working with SANRAL and other agencies that may assist the investigation to bring those responsible to book. -TNA Reporter     